Match the dock blur mask corner radius to the skin background in the Tahoe skins.

The blur region is rounded using `blurRadius`, which is NOT the blur strength
(that is a global KWin setting) but only the corner rounding of the mask fed to
KWindowEffects::enableBlurBehind. Both Tahoe skins used blurRadius = 24 while the
bg*.png background has a corner radius of ~16px, so the frosted region bulged ~8px
past the (semi-transparent) rounded background at every corner and showed up as a
bright, unblurred-tinted "nub" poking out of the dock corners over the wallpaper.

Set blurRadius = 16 so the blur mask corners coincide with the background corners:
nothing pokes out, and the corners stay blurred (matching, not smaller, so the
translucent corner never reveals a sharp wallpaper edge).

The trailing tabs after the file names in the --- / +++ lines are required so that
patch(1) does not truncate the "Tahoe Dark" path at the space.
--- a/package/contents/skins/Tahoe Dark/Config.qml	
+++ b/package/contents/skins/Tahoe Dark/Config.qml	
@@ -8,7 +8,7 @@ QtObject {
     property string imageRight: "bgr.png"
     property string imagetask: "tasks.svgz"
     property bool blur: true
-    property int blurRadius: 24
+    property int blurRadius: 16
     property int positionTaskIndicator: 9
     property int leftMargin: 20
     property int topMargin: 20
--- a/package/contents/skins/Tahoe/Config.qml	
+++ b/package/contents/skins/Tahoe/Config.qml	
@@ -8,7 +8,7 @@ QtObject {
     property string imageRight: "bgr.png"
     property string imagetask: "tasks.svgz"
     property bool blur: true
-    property int blurRadius: 24
+    property int blurRadius: 16
     property int positionTaskIndicator: 9
     property int leftMargin: 20
     property int topMargin: 20
